<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,242,752]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,381,405]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Remarks:</emphasis>
According to Rosalie de Lamarck, there was only 
<specimenCount box="[887,1040,381,405]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
in her father’s collection. Lamarck stated a size of 16 lignes et demie (= 
<quantity box="[592,699,415,439]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.72" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="mm" value="37.2">37.2 mm</quantity>
). The 
<specimenCount box="[774,942,415,439]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
in the Lamarck collection were chosen by Mermod from a series of many specimens labeled 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bruguiere" baseAuthorityYear="1789" box="[728,908,451,475]" class="Gastropoda" family="Clavatulidae" genus="Pusionella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="nifat">
<emphasis box="[728,908,451,475]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Pusionella nifat</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the Delessert collection. In the handwritten card file that he made for the Lamarck collection, Mermod noted that among the specimens which were in the Delessert collection, one matches 
<bibRefCitation author="Lamarck's" box="[549,734,519,543]" firstAuthor="Lamarck's" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="1 - 16" refId="ref11163" refString="Lamarck, [J. B. P. A] (1816) Mollusques et polypes divers In: Bruguiere et al., 1791 - 1827: Tableau encyclopedique et methodique des trois regnes de la nature. Part 23: 1 - 16, pls. 391 - 488, 431 bis, 431 bis *. [Pp. 1 - 16, Liste des objects representes dans les planches de cette livraison, are plate captions only, lacking in many copies of part 23]. [See also Petit, 2011 and Matsukuma, 2012]." type="journal article" year="1816">Lamarck’s 1816</bibRefCitation>
figure and also matches the 1822 description fairly well. It further matches the size (about 
<quantity box="[518,600,554,578]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.7" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="mm" value="37.0">37 mm</quantity>
) given by Lamarck in (1822). This would mean that the note applies to specimen 1098/41/2 (
<quantity box="[392,498,589,613]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.65" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="mm" value="36.5">36.5 mm</quantity>
), but subsequently Mermod labeled only the larger specimen 1098/41/1 (
<quantity box="[1316,1397,589,613]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.6" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="mm" value="46.0">46 mm</quantity>
) as “ 
<typeStatus box="[162,216,623,647]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">type</typeStatus>
”. He also added that the 
<specimenCount box="[511,652,623,647]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="generic">2 specimens</specimenCount>
selected were placed with doubt in the Lamarck collection because neither of them matches Kiener’s figures.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,242,752]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,542,693,718]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Current taxonomic position:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="(Bruguiere, 1789)" baseAuthorityName="Bruguiere" baseAuthorityYear="1789" box="[551,945,693,717]" class="Gastropoda" family="Clavatulidae" genus="Pusionella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="nifat">
<emphasis box="[551,731,693,717]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Pusionella nifat</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bruguiere" box="[747,937,693,717]" firstAuthor="Bruguiere" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="1 - 344" refId="ref9515" refString="Bruguiere, J. G. (1789) Histoire naturelle des Vers. In: Encyclopedie methodique, Vol. 1, part 1, [i] - xviii, pp. 1 - 344. Paris: Panckoucke." type="journal article" year="1789">Bruguière, 1789</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
; placed in synonymy with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bruguiere" baseAuthorityYear="1789" box="[1256,1435,693,717]" class="Gastropoda" family="Clavatulidae" genus="Pusionella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="nifat">
<emphasis box="[1256,1435,693,717]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Pusionella nifat</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. Adams &amp; A. Adams" authorityYear="1853" box="[157,261,727,751]" class="Gastropoda" family="Turridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Turridae</taxonomicName>
], the 
<typeStatus box="[320,368,728,752]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Gray, 1847" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1847" box="[493,746,727,752]" class="Gastropoda" family="Clavatulidae" genus="Pusionella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[493,613,728,752]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Pusionella</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Gray" box="[620,746,727,751]" firstAuthor="Gray" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="129 - 219" refId="ref10473" refString="Gray, J. E. (1847) A list of the genera of Recent Mollusca, their synonyms and types. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London for, 1847, 129 - 219." type="journal article" year="1847">Gray, 1847</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, by Tryon (1881): 271. Locality is West Africa.
</paragraph>
